  "primerTitle": "Cyrillic (Russian) alphabet — quick recap",
  "primer": "The Russian Cyrillic alphabet has **33 letters**, each with an **uppercase** and **lowercase** form. A useful way in is by relation to Latin: some letters *look and sound* the same, some are **false friends** (look Latin but sound different), and some are entirely new shapes. Two letters (Ъ, Ь) carry **no sound** of their own — they modify the preceding consonant.\n\n**Same as Latin (look + sound match):**\n- **А а** — a (as in 'car')\n- **К к** — k\n- **М м** — m\n- **О о** — o (as in 'or')\n- **Т т** — t\n\n**False friends (look Latin, sound different):**\n- **В в** — v (not 'b')\n- **Е е** — ye (as in 'yes')\n- **Н н** — n (not 'h')\n- **Р р** — r, rolled (not 'p')\n- **С с** — s (not 'c')\n- **У у** — u (as in 'boot'; not 'y')\n- **Х х** — kh (Scottish 'loch'; not 'x')\n\n**New shapes:**\n- **Б б** — b\n- **Г г** — g (hard, 'go')\n- **Д д** — d\n- **Ё ё** — yo (as in 'yonder'); always stressed\n- **Ж ж** — zh (like 's' in 'measure')\n- **З з** — z\n- **И и** — i (ee, as in 'meet')\n- **Й й** — y (short, as in 'boy'); a glide\n- **Л л** — l\n- **П п** — p (like Greek π)\n- **Ф ф** — f\n- **Ц ц** — ts (as in 'cats')\n- **Ч ч** — ch (as in 'church')\n- **Ш ш** — sh (as in 'shop')\n- **Щ щ** — shch (long, soft 'sh')\n- **Ъ ъ** — hard sign — *no sound*; keeps the consonant hard before a vowel\n- **Ы ы** — y — a tense, back 'i' (like 'i' in 'ill'); no English equivalent\n- **Ь ь** — soft sign — *no sound*; softens (palatalises) the preceding consonant\n- **Э э** — e (as in 'end'); the 'hard' e without the 'y' glide of Е\n- **Ю ю** — yu (as in 'universe')\n- **Я я** — ya (as in 'yard')\n\n**Special cases:** the *iotated* vowels Е, Ё, Ю, Я carry a 'y' glide; Э is the plain 'e' counterpart of Е; Ъ and Ь are silent modifiers; the dots on Ё are often dropped in print.",
